Create and test an XHTML document that displays a table of football scores from a collegiate 
football conference in which the team names
have one of the primary colors of their respective schools. 
The winning scores must appear larger and in a different font than the losing scores. 
The team names must be in a script font.






<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Football Scores</title>
</head>

<body>

<h2>Collegiate Football Conference Scores</h2>

<table border="1" cellpadding="8">

<tr>
    <th>Team</th>
    <th>Score</th>
</tr>

<tr>
    <td style="color:blue; font-family:cursive;">Blue Team</td>
    <td style="font-size:20px; font-family:Arial;"><b>35</b></td>
</tr>

<tr>
    <td style="color:red; font-family:cursive;">Red Team</td>
    <td style="font-size:14px; font-family:'Times New Roman';">21</td>
</tr>

<tr>
    <td style="color:green; font-family:cursive;">Green Team</td>
    <td style="font-size:14px; font-family:'Times New Roman';">14</td>
</tr>

<tr>
    <td style="color:gold; font-family:cursive;">Yellow Team</td>
    <td style="font-size:20px; font-family:Arial;"><b>42</b></td>
</tr>

</table>

</body>
</html>
